name: Antique Moroccan Hand-Carved Stool with Custom Linen Upholstery, Circa 1900

condition.details: Reupholstered. Wear consistent with age and use. Please refer to the various additional photos for further condition details and contact us with any questions!

specifications.rawSpecificationsHTML: This circa 1900 Moroccan stool showcases intricate hand-carved details and delicate bone inlay, creating a striking contrast against the rich wood. The geometric and arabesque motifs reflect traditional Moroccan artistry, while the custom linen-upholstered seat, finished with a row of brass nailheads, adds a refined touch. The openwork base enhances its airy yet structured aesthetic, making it a timeless addition to any space. Versatile in function, this Moroccan stool serves beautifully as a decorative accent, footstool, or additional seating in a living room, bedroom, or entryway. Its compact size allows it to be tucked under a console or placed beside a low-slung lounge chair, offering both practicality and elegance. The fusion of bone inlay and carved details makes it a statement piece that pairs effortlessly with eclectic, bohemian, or traditional interiors. Whether used as a stylish ottoman or a distinctive side table, this stool embodies Moroccan heritage and craftsmanship, bringing warmth and character to any setting.
